Question-1: 

Create a file  httpd.yml so that

	1)	 It should create a directory named   /var/www/html/public
	
	2)	Make sure to copy the file from https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ahmedabad/rapid-test-at-home-kits-flying-off-the-shelves/articleshow/88783483.cms and copy it to /var/www/html/public
	
	3) Give proper permissions to that file so that all other users can read it
	
	4)  Install apache
	
	5) Replace all entries of "AllowOverride None" with "AllowOverride AuthConfig" in the file /etc/apache2/apache2/conf  using the replace module
	++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
	
