Question-3:

Create a file adh.yaml so that

	a) This should copy the file /usr/local/bin/runme.sh to /usr/bin/runme.sh on all nodes.

	b) This should run as user root user.

	c) The file should have execute permissions.

	d} file should be owned by ubuntu user.
	

Question-4:

Create a file called authoriazation.yaml so that

	a) It should check the content of  http://classroom.example.com/access
	
	b) If the url is accessible it should create a file named /var/www/html/access.html with the content of  http://classroom.example.com/access.

	c) Otherwise it should create a file nocontent.html with the content as “I have no access”. Inaccessible
   

